NAME
     afatofm - convert an alternating finite automaton to a _f_m

SYNOPSIS
     afatofm afa

     afatofm < afa

DESCRIPTION
     afatofm reads in a given alternating finite  state  machine,
     convert  it to an equivalent _d_e_t_e_r_m_i_n_i_s_t_i_c _f_i_n_i_t_e _a_u_t_o_m_a_t_o_n,
     and then writes the _d_f_a on the standard ouput.

     _a_f_a must conform to the Grail bit-wise format for  alternat-
     ing finite state machines.  afatofm doesn't necessarily con-
     vert  _a_f_a to a complete finite state machine.  The resulting
     machine can only be ensureed to be deterministic

EXAMPLES
          % cat bitafa1
          symbols: [a,b]
          states:  3
          finals:  5
          head: 7 4
          7 5
          7 1
          0 1
          3 1
          6 2
          7 3

          % afatofm bitafa1
          (START) |- 5
          5 a 1
          5 b 2
          2 a 4
          2 b 0
          0 a 0
          0 b 0
          4 a 0
          4 b 0
          1 a 0
          1 b 3
          3 a 4
          3 b 4
          4 -| (FINAL)

          % afatofm < bitafa1
          (START) |- 5
          5 a 1
          5 b 2
          2 a 4



